Remember to be alert at all times.
Stay aware of your surroundings.
Take AR photos when you feed your Pikmin and share them with your friends!
The detector will be recharged with one free use every day if it’s empty, so don’t forget to use it up!
Feed nectar to your Pikmin every day to raise their friendship level and increase their strength!
Add your favorite photos and write about your day in the lifelog. Tap the button on the lower left to get started.
Long tap to select multiple items in your Pikmin or postcard lists.
Pikmin who have come to deliver postcards will wait up to three days until they are received.
Plant flowers around a big flower to help it bloom.
Big flowers shine bright in the first hour of blooming. Try planting flowers around one and maybe you will find a nice surprise!
Seedlings grow faster while planting flowers. Plant flowers to collect more and more Pikmin!
Get bonus coins while planting flowers.
Set up privacy zones from the settings screen to exclude certain areas where you don't want to plant flowers.
You can delete flowers that you have planted from your lifelog or the settings screen.
Invite your friends to join Pikmin Bloom and get rewards!
Check out the help section from the settings screen if you have any questions.
Use the sorting function in your Pikmin list to find your Pikmin more easily.
Link your Nintendo Account to receive a special seedling! Go to the settings screen or the Mii customization screen.
Want to swap all the Pikmin in your squad at once? Quickly tap the whistle two times, and they will be replaced by standby Pikmin.
Special slots allow seedlings to grow faster than usual. You can buy them at the store.
It seems the items worn by Decor Pikmin are related to the location where their seedling was found. Go to the seedling details screen to find out the details.
Too busy to feed your Pikmin nectar one at a time? Try dragging the nectar icon toward them.
When your Pikmin lose the flowers on their heads, add them to your squad and take them out for a walk. That seems to help them recover their leaves faster.
Check the types of Decor Pikmin you have found so far from the Decor Pikmin badge details screen.
Long tap a Pikmin in to pick them up. You can also use the magnifying glass to observe them.
Collect nectar from big flowers that are in bloom! Open the details screen and swipe down the flower.
When you want to give nectar to a specific Pikmin, double-tap to zoom in on them.
Give special nectar to your favorite Pikmin to give a big boost to your friendship level!
You can upgrade your storage capacity for Pikmin, seedlings, nectar and petals from the store.
Tap the big map on the home screen to access your lifelog, expeditions, postcards, Pikmin list and more!
Expedition items will disappear if you don't send Pikmin to retrieve them. Items are listed from oldest to newest, so get the ones you want before they are gone.
Winged Pikmin seem to be very fast in expeditions, unless they go with other types of Pikmin.
When tackling mushroom battles, Pikmin of the same color as the mushroom, Decor Pikmin, and Pikmin with flowers seem to be the most powerful.
Clear mushroom battles as fast as you can to get higher ratings and better rewards!
You can get seasonal flower nectars in the mushroom battle fruit rewards.
Feed your Pikmin nectar and send them on expeditions and mushrooms to raise their friendship level.
Some big flowers may bloom only during certain seasons. Check the news section to see what flowers are in season this month.
Make friends to send each other postcards and check out each other's steps, Pikmin, and badges.
When you walk through a new place, the white clouds on the map will clear away to reveal the new location. Use the map to see the places you have visited so far.
Help your friends by gifting them some useful items! Visit the shop for more details.
Already cleared the weekly challenge? Use a weekly challenge ticket to play again!
Use the mushroom recharge ticket to join mushroom battles that already have 5 participants. Up to 20 players can join.
Use the mushroom recharge ticket when you’ve run out of daily mushroom battle tries.
The flower planting accelerator doubles your flower planting speed for a certain period of time. Use to quickly clear flower-planting missions!
Check out your weekly lookback every Sunday in the lifelog.
You can give nectar to specific Pikmin in the Pikmin List. Tap the Pikmin you want to feed and select the nectar icon.
When a Pikmin has more than 4 friendship hearts, they will be displayed in yellow. The more hearts you have, the stronger your Pikmin becomes.
Pikmin decor category icons in yellow indicate that decor Pikmin has already been registered in your decor list.
Want to share your new Pikmin with your friends? Go to the Pikmin's detail screen anytime to share!

Achievements unlocked! These will help you make progress as you play.
You can now collect stamps to unlock new things.
Try to complete as many Achievements as you can!
In AR Mode, you can interact with your Pikmin in the real world.
Point your camera at a flat surface so your Pikmin can gather there!
Once your Pikmin appear, you can play with them!
If a Pikmin blooms too many flowers in one day, it will get tired and be unable to grow more.
Bare Pikmin are too tired to eat nectar—but there's no need to worry!
Pikmin will regrow their leaves each morning, and will be refreshed and ready to explore! But they'll have to rest until then.
After a Pikmin's flower has bloomed a number of times, they'll be very tired and will turn back into a seedling.
They'll still remember the time they spent with you though. And something good might happen when they're regrown!
If a Pikmin turns back into a seedling, just grow them again!
When you achieve certain goals in Pikmin Bloom, you'll be presented with a badge as proof.
The badges you've earned will be shown in your profile. You can check the record you achieved and your next goal from the details screen.
Each badge has various ranks. The higher the rank, the harder it is to earn. Some are quite challenging, but you can do it!
It looks like Pikmin can grow different colors and types of flowers based on the type of nectar they eat.
Tap on the Nectar to switch to a different type. Try giving your Pikmin different types of nectar and see what happens.
Once you have created your own Party Walk, share the invite code with your friends and family and invite them to participate! You can view the code at any time from the Party Walk Details screen.
While hosting a Party Walk, you might receive friend requests from participants. Expand your circle and enjoy playing Pikmin Bloom together!
After 9:00 p.m. each day, you'll be able to view your daily lookback! If you miss it, go to the main screen or the lifelog to check it out.
The daily lookback is the animation where you can see your step count, the places you visited during the day, and leave a record in your lifelog.
Your Pikmin may also choose one of the pictures you took that day. If you like, you can keep it on your lifelog.
If you want Pikmin to look for pictures, they'll need access to your photo library, so grant them permission if you'd like their help!
Go to the settings screen to change the time your daily lookback plays every day.
Congratulations! You found a Decor Pikmin!
Decor Pikmin are rarer than other types... Their appearance is based on the area they were discovered.
You can easily see what varieties of Decor Pikmin you've found by tapping the related badge in your profile.
Depending on where you find the Pikmin seedlings, they will wear different items. Try growing Pikmin in many different places!
You can now add and change your name. This name will be used to refer to you and will be displayed throughout the game. You can change your name in the settings page.
You can now send your Pikmin on distant expeditions!
Items can appear where you have walked on the map... sometimes even rare seedlings and fruits!
To send Pikmin on an expedition, select the item, then pick the Pikmin you want to send. Then, just wait for their return.
The time it takes to complete an expedition varies depending on what Pikmin you send. Try experimenting with different squads!
You can play the flower planting challenges in groups of up to 5 people.
Your friends and your friend’s friends can participate in the group.
During the challenge, group members can see each other's names, planted flower counts and types, etc.
To form bigger groups, you can invite friends or join groups your friends are in.
Enjoy planting flowers with your friends, no matter how far away they are!
In the flower planting challenges, when someone plants 1,000 flowers, everyone gets petals as a teamwork bonus.
Every now and then, check in on everyone's hard work through the Challenge screen!
You can play the flower planting challenges in groups of up to 5 people.
Your friends and your friend’s friends can participate in the group.

You can choose from the following two groups.
① Friends’ Group
② Anyone Can Join Group

① Friends’ Group:
Besides your friends, your friend’s friends can also join this group. Work with friends to clear the goal!

② Anyone Can Join Group:
If you want to make more friends, we highly recommend this group! Now you can create a group with users who are not your friends and send them friend requests.
You may not invite friends to join a group with anyone. Please note that the challenge period may be shorter depending on the time difference between you and the members of the group you joined.
Whilst you have flower planting mode on, flowers will grow around you as you walk.
While you're planting flowers, petals you've collected from your Pikmin will be used up, one by one.
Flowers will be planted even while the app is closed, and they'll stop when you run out. You can also stop planting at any time.
Other users will be able to see the flowers you plant. (You can set your "Privacy Zones" from the settings screen.)
The huge flower you can see in walk view is called a Big Flower.
Pikmin can help this flower grow even bigger by planting flowers around it. What kind of nectar would a blossom like that produce?

Big flowers can blossom into all kinds of flowers, and rumor has it that the type of 
flowers planted nearby has something to do with it. Try planting different types of flowers around them and see what happens!
You can join other players via the "With Others" mode and plant flowers together!
Players who are planting flowers with others will be able to see each other on screen.
Your Mii and location will be visible to others, so please keep the planting to safe public spaces.
By using the petals to plant flowers, the environment grows gradually more comfortable for your Pikmin.
On top of earning more points from each step, you'll also be able to grow seedlings faster while planting flowers.
When you plant flowers with others, other players can appear on your screen. Have fun planting together!
Working together with Pikmin, we can help create a more flower-filled world!
Big flowers glow when they are in full bloom. That means they are full of nectar!
To collect the nectar, swipe vertically across the big flower.
Once the extract is collected, the flower stops glowing. You will be able to collect more nectar when the flower is in full bloom again.
Visit different places and collect nectar from as many big flowers as you can!
After a Pikmin earns 4 hearts, you can develop their friendship even further.
Further hearts represent an even deeper level of friendship, and are filled with a brilliant yellow. The more of these hearts a Pikmin has, the higher their strength will be.
From freshly plucked Pikmin to those that have been with you from the beginning, try deepening your bond even further!
The more you interact with your Pikmin, the more your friendship level will increase.
Your friendship level will increase as you feed your Pikmin nectar and send them on expeditions.
When your friendship level with a Pikmin reaches four hearts, they may give you a special souvenir from the place they were born!
Be sure to keep an eye on your friendship level!
Now you can play the weekly challenge!
Complete the weekly missions by the deadline to earn rewards!
Work together with your friends to complete difficult challenges.
Make more friends and try the weekly challenges!
Now you can join the “Anyone Can Join Group” where you can play with others who are not your friends!

※ You can’t invite friends to the "Group With Anyone" .
※ Please note that your playing time might be shorter than the other players depending on when you join the challenge.
You can view planted flowers and big flowers in AR flower mode. Flowers must be within a certain radius from your location.
You got some gold seedling fragments! Once you gather 10,000 of them, they will transform into a gold seedling.
You can get gold seedlings from places like your daily lookback and milestones.
You can confirm how many you have from the seedling list. Keep playing Pikmin Bloom to gather more gold seedling fragments!
By collecting 10,000 fragments, you've obtained a rare gold seedling!
Gold seedlings will always grow into a Pikmin wearing something related to the place they are planted.
When you get a gold seedling, try planting it in one of your favorite places!

A limited time Halloween mushroom has appeared!
The Jack-o'-lantern decor Pikmin are the strongest against these mushrooms.
You can try sending regular Pikmin, but the battle could take a very long time.
You can now access your friend list from the home screen.
Collect the fruit that your Pikmin gather while walking to get more Honey.
Different fruits yield different amounts of Honey.
Try to get as much Honey as you can to feed your Pikmin!
Your daily activity is automatically recorded to your lifelog!
Looking back on your logged days, you see the places you visited, any pictures you kept, and your step counts.
If something special happens, you can save pictures and notes to remember it by.
By saving your special moments, you'll be able to look back on them later!
You can see and share your memento cards in your lifelog.
New event challenges! Participate to get rewards such as limited-edition Decor Pikmin seedlings and game items!
For each mission you clear, you will get a chance to win a random reward.

Your progress in the challenges will make the big flower in that stage bloom. 
When the big flower is in full bloom, you will get a gold seedling!

There's a total of four stages in the event challenges. 
You will know you've cleared all of them when you make the big flower in stage 4 go into full bloom. 
You can also replay from the beginning when you clear all of the stages.

Congrats! 
You got a rare reward and a special chance to double it!
And no need to worry about item storage limits! They will not apply when you double your reward.
You can now give nectar to Pikmin directly from the mushroom screen.
Pikmin with flowers have higher strength. Try feeding nectar to your Pikmin before going to a mushroom battle!
During a mushroom battle, you can press the 'Call Friends for Help' button to ask your friends to join the battle.
With 1 bullhorn you can request up to 4 friends for help. Even after it has been used, you can still change friends in battle.
Friends who are sent a help request will be able to join that mushroom from a distance. Up to 10 help requests received will be displayed.
Join forces with your friends and destroy as many mushrooms as you can!
Sending Pikmin with higher total strength will destroy mushrooms faster and raise your score when you clear them.

There are a few conditions for high Pikmin strength:
・Matching Pikmin colors to Mushroom colors
・Wearing a decor
・Growing a seasonal flower
・Having a high friendship level
The more players participating, the higher your total Pikmin strength will reach. By helping players in need, you can aim for a score higher than you can get alone!
You can see info about other participants by tapping on their Mii icon from the Mushroom details screen.
You can now set your flower planting Privacy Zones from the settings screen!

Privacy zones are areas where flowers won’t be planted when you walk in flower planting mode.
Your privacy zones only apply to you, and won’t affect other users.
If you walk within your privacy zone while planting flowers, flower petals will be consumed over time as usual. The flower planting boost will also be effective.
Make use of privacy zones, and enjoy flower planting with peace of mind!
You can now share cards of your newly plucked Pikmin. Introduce your new Pikmin to your friends!
It requires more steps to grow, but a special Pikmin is more likely to sprout.
Keep planting seedlings. There's so much to discover!
It requires more steps to grow, but you might get a rare Pikmin from it.
Keep planting these Seedlings. There's so much to discover!
Pikmin are mysterious creatures, neither plant nor animal.
Pikmin follow you, picking up Seedlings and fruit along the way.
After planting a Seedling, you can grow it by walking (even without having the app open). Turning on notifications will help to remind you of your progress!
It's time to play Pikmin Bloom! Walk and explore to grow Pikmin and cover the world in flowers!
You can check each Pikmin's details screen from the Memories Log.
Friendship level: When you take your Pikmin on walks and give them Honey, their friendship level will increase.
Flower types: You can check the types of flowers this Pikmin can bloom.
You can check this screen whenever you pluck a new Pikmin!
As you play Pikmin Bloom, you will eventually level up.
As your level goes up, so does the number of Pikmin you can have in your squad. You will also be able to unlock other new features.
For more information on your level, check out your in-game profile.
For more information on your level, check out your in-game profile.
This Pikmin has a postcard for you!
Postcards include commemorative photos of places and things your Pikmin discovered while they were out.
Each postcard is special and features the Pikmin who were sent out on the expedition. Be sure to cherish it!
Even if you close the app, push notifications will keep you informed about the growth of your seedlings.
Allow push notifications to better enjoy Pikmin Bloom.

Congratulations on completing a Decor!
You've unlocked Rare Decor Levels that allow you to meet Rare Decor Pikmin.
Rare Gifts will appear when you level up a Rare Decor Level. If you send a Pikmin from that decor category, they'll change into a Rare Decor Pikmin!
Get points to level up your Rare Decor Level in the following ways.

・Pulling out a seedling from that category.
・Turning a Pikmin from that category into a Decor Pikmin.
・Releasing a Pikmin from that category.
You can now find mushroom battles in the walk view! Sending as many Pikmin as you can to destroy the mushrooms!
When the mushrooms are destroyed, your Pikmin's friendship level will increase and you will receive a reward.
The mushroom battle allows up to 5 participants at a time, but with a mushroom recharge ticket, up to 20 people can join in on the action.
You can find mushrooms in the walk view or the expedition list. If you don't see any mushrooms around you, go out and find some!
The higher your level, the more Pikmin you will be able to send. Work together and send as many Pikmin as you can!
You can't hold any more seedlings! When you get a new seedling, it will replace an old one.
Favorite the seedlings you want to keep in your inventory.
This is a new feature called Party Walk! In this special walking content, you can have lots of people walking with you. Let’s start by checking out the Challenge List!
You’ve joined a Party Walk! Let’s get walking! You’ll receive a special Memento Card once it's finished!
You can also host your own Party Walk! You can host 1 Party Walk and participate in 3 others at the same time.
Walk results will be deleted after 14 days. However, you can revisit your Memento Cards through the Lifelog.
While participating in a Party Walk, you might receive friend requests from other participants. Expand your circle and enjoy playing Pikmin Bloom together!
Party Walk is special content that you can host too! Everyone gets a special Memento Card at the end, so let's walk together a lot.
By the way, you can also host a Party Walk! Create a new Walk from your Challenge List.
Create your own Party Walk, share the invite code with friends and family, and invite participants! You can host 1 Party Walk and participate in 3 others at the same time.
Walk results will be deleted after 14 days. However, you can revisit your Memento Cards through the Lifelog.
While participating in a Party Walk, you might receive friend requests from other participants. Expand your circle and enjoy playing Pikmin Bloom together!
It's time to join a Party Walk! Partake in special content where you can walk alongside your admired celebrities. Register to participate on the next page and join the excitement!
Step Tanks are useful items that store energy from your steps as you carry them.
When you've taken 1,000 steps with one, you can use it to grow a seedling in your Planter Pack.
You can get Step Tanks from the in-game shop. Use them to grow lots of Pikmin!
Once your squad is full, new Pikmin will be placed on standby.
New Pikmin will be added to your squad as space opens up. To keep a certain Pikmin in your squad, make sure to mark it as a favorite.
As you gain levels, the number of Pikmin you can have in your squad goes up. Keep leveling up to walk with lots of Pikmin!
It's time to play the Star Challenge! Embark on a special challenge where you can walk alongside your admired celebrities. Register to participate on the next page and join the excitement!
You can send balloons to everyone in the group as a sign of support.
You will get more balloons for every 1000 steps you take. Go on a walk and get more balloons!
Every balloon sent during the challenge will be displayed to the challenge host. Send some to show your support!
You can play the weekly challenges in groups of up to 5 people.
Your friends and your friend’s friends can participate in the group.
During the challenge, group members can see each other's names, step counts, etc. You can also send friend requests to other participants.
You can join group challenges even after the group has started playing.
Let's work together to clear the goal!
You can play the weekly challenges in groups of up to 5 people.
In addition to your friends, friends of friends can also join groups.
During a challenge, group members can see each others' names, step counts, etc.
Play with more people by inviting friends to your group, or joining groups your friends are already participating in.
Work together with others and try to clear the goal!
Challenges have been improved! ・You can now invite friends! ・If you leave a challenge, you can join a different one! * Caution: When you leave a challenge, your progress up to now will be erased.
You can play the weekly challenges in groups of up to 5 people. During a challenge, group members can see each others' names, step counts, etc.

You can choose from the following two groups.
① Friends’ Group
② Anyone Can Join Group

① Friends’ Group:
Besides your friends, your friend’s friends can also join this group. Work with friends to clear the goal!
You can join groups your friends are already in, or invite your friends to new groups.

② Anyone Can Join Group:
If you want to make more friends, we highly recommend this group! Now you can create a group with users who are not your friends and send them friend requests.
You may not invite friends to join a group with anyone. Please note that the challenge period may be shorter depending on the time difference between you and the members of the group you joined.
Here's your weekly lookback! Here, you can view your steps taken and the places you visited week by week.
Weekly lookbacks are available after viewing your daily lookback each Sunday. You can also view them from your lifelog!
You can give instructions to Pikmin in the garden by blowing your whistle.
Try to press and hold the whistle. Pikmin in the garden will gather when they hear it.
Practice using your whistle to command your Pikmin!
In addition to gathering your Pikmin, you can also use your whistle to manage your squad.
Try double-tapping the whistle. Your squad will automatically organize themselves.
Practice using your whistle to give your Pikmin directions!
